<scenario>
The agent A provided the following violation scenario:
The pointer parameter 'c' (type 'struct MHD_Connection *') is only read in this function — e.g. const uint64_t since_actv = now - c->last_activity; — therefore it should be a pointer-to-const (e.g. const struct MHD_Connection *c). Declaring the parameter non-const when it is never used to modify the object violates MISRA C 2023 Rule 8.13.
</scenario>

